claim.claim-text:
1. A method of treating a patient suffering from hypertension or hypertensive crises, said method comprising the steps of:
a) determining, based on an evaluation of the patient, that the patient is suffering from hypertension or hypertensive crises;
b) determining the skin type of the patient;
c) determining and selecting a therapeutically effective dosage of artificial UV-A ultraviolet light based on the condition of the patient and the skin type of the patient;
d) administering to said patient said selected dosage of artificial UV-A ultraviolet light; and
e) measuring the blood pressure of said patient within 30 minutes of the conclusion of said administering step.
